    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The Aguada culture developed in the border region between the Argentine provinces of Catamarca and La Rioja, between 600 and 900 CE;  its influence is seen in northwestern Argentina and northern parts of Chile.</Note_Text>
